LAGOS – In order to motivate fans to troop out en mass to the Moshood Abiola National Stadium in Abuja to support the Super Eagles against the Black Stars of Ghana on Tuesday, the Orji Uzor Kalu Foundation has reportedly purchased 5000 tickets for fans. According to information obtained, the Foundation purchased that number of tickets for interested fans who would be available to support the Super Eagles. In a press release he personally signed, Kalu said: “The tickets will be shared at the entrance of the stadium by 1 PM and “as African Pillar of Sports, I look forward to the Eagles putting smiles on our faces by winning the match.” Meanwhile, the Minister of Federal Capital Territory has allocated 100 buses for free transportation of spectators from every part of Abuja to MKO Abiola Stadium on the day of the return match. Sixty thousand fans will be allowed into the stadium to watch the second leg of the 2022 World Cup Qualifier between the two West African giants.